has an error where if for some reason a file has disapeared from the filesystem, but exists in the cache, this line fails on `mini.width` with an uncaught Exception:

```
Exception Value:    
'NoneType' object is not subscriptable
Exception Location: /path/to/venv/lib/python2.7/site-packages/sorl/thumbnail/images.py in width, line 51
```

Reverting the model field to a regular (non-sorl) image field clears up the issue. 

A fix may include  wrapping the Exception's else which while a little dirty allows fallback to a working state.

```
def render(self, name, value, attrs=None):
    output = super(AdminImageWidget, self).render(name, value, attrs)
    if value and hasattr(value, 'url'):
        try:
            mini = get_thumbnail(value, 'x80', upscale=False)
        except Exception as e:
            logger.warn("Unable to get the thumbnail", exc_info=e)
        else:
            try:
                output = (
                             '<div style="float:left">'
                             '<a style="width:%spx;display:block;margin:0 0 10px" class="thumbnail" target="_blank" href="%s">'
                             '<img src="%s"></a>%s</div>'
                         ) % (mini.width, value.url, mini.url, output)
            except:
                pass
    return mark_safe(output)
```

